[2026-05-19T00:17:52.729Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_qumz5ptk1ypc_1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Task: 006-weight-nutrition-03-convert\n2\t\n3\t# Convert: Weight & Nutrition\n4\t\n5\tConvert the constrained HTML design to a pixel-perfect Flutter widget using the **stitch-flutter** skill.\n6\t\n7\t## Inputs\n8\t- `.stitch/designs/weight-nutrition/design.html` — HTML design mockup (written in Flutter HTML Glossary vocabulary)\n9\t- `.stitch/designs/weight-nutrition/SPEC.md` — Screen specification\n10\t- `.stitch/system/DESIGN.md` — Design system specification\n11\t\n12\t## How It Works\n13\t\n14\tThe HTML mockup uses the **Flutter HTML Glossary** — a constrained vocabulary where every HTML class and `data-*` attribute maps 1:1 to a Flutter widget. This enables mechanical, pixel-perfect conversion.\n15\t\n16\t## Conversion Steps\n17\t\n18\t1. **Read HTML** — Parse `.stitch/designs/weight-nutrition/design.html` and extract:\n19\t   - `:root` CSS tokens → update `lib/theme/app_theme.dart` if new tokens found\n20\t   - `.scaffold` element tree → this is the conversion entry point\n21\t   - `data-*` attributes → Flutter widget parameters\n22\t   - `data-animate` attributes → `flutter_animate` chains\n23\t   - `aria-*` attributes → `Semantics` widgets\n24\t\n25\t2. **Walk the DOM** — Process each glossary element top-down:\n26\t   - `.scaffold` → `Scaffold()`\n27\t   - `.app-bar` → `AppBar()`\n28\t   - `.column` → `Column()`\n29\t   - `.row` → `Row()`\n30\t   - `.card` → `Card()`\n31\t   - `.ink-well[data-route]` → `InkWell(onTap: () => context.push(route))`\n32\t   - `.network-image` → `CachedNetworkImage()`\n33\t   - `.icon[data-name]` → `Icon(Icons.{name})`\n34\t   - Text classes (`.title-large`, `.body-medium`, etc.) → `Text(..., style: textTheme.X)`\n35\t   - `data-color` → `colorScheme.X`\n36\t   - `data-spacing` → `AppTheme.spaceX`\n37\t   - `data-radius` → `AppTheme.radiusX`\n38\t\n39\t3. **Generate Dart** — Write `lib/screens/weight_nutrition/weight_nutrition_screen.dart`:\n40\t   ```dart\n41\t   import 'package:flutter/material.dart';\n42\t   import 'package:cached_network_image/cached_network_image.dart';\n43\t   import 'package:flutter_animate/flutter_animate.dart';\n44\t   import 'package:folio/theme/app_theme.dart';\n45\t\n46\t   class WeightNutritionScreen extends StatelessWidget {\n47\t     const WeightNutritionScreen({super.key});\n48\t\n49\t     @override\n50\t     Widget build(BuildContext context) {\n51\t       final theme = Theme.of(context);\n52\t       final colorScheme = theme.colorScheme;\n53\t       final textTheme = theme.textTheme;\n54\t\n55\t       return Scaffold(\n56\t         // ... mechanically converted from glossary elements\n57\t       );\n58\t     }\n59\t   }\n60\t   ```\n61\t\n62\t4. **Update router** — Add route to `lib/router/app_router.dart`:\n63\t   ```dart\n64\t   GoRoute(\n65\t     path: '/weight-nutrition',\n66\t     builder: (context, state) => const WeightNutritionScreen(),\n67\t   ),\n68\t   ```\n69\t\n70\t5. **Verify** — Run `dart analyze lib/screens/weight_nutrition/weight_nutrition_screen.dart`\n71\t\n72\t## Reference Skills\n73\t\n74\t- Read **flutter-building-layouts** for constraint rules (constraints down, sizes up), avoiding unbounded constraints in flex boxes, and when to use `Expanded` vs `Flexible` vs `SizedBox`.\n75\t- Read **flutter-animating-apps** for Hero transition setup, implicit vs explicit animations, and staggered animation patterns.\n76\t\n77\t## Quality Gates\n78\t\n79\t- **No hardcoded colors** — `Color(0xFF...)` and `Colors.blue` are banned; use `colorScheme.X`\n80\t- **No hardcoded text styles** — `TextStyle(fontSize: 16)` is banned; use `textTheme.X`\n81\t- **No hardcoded spacing** — `EdgeInsets.all(16)` is banned; use `AppTheme.spaceMd`\n82\t- **No Container abuse** — prefer `SizedBox`, `Padding`, `DecoratedBox` when Container is overkill\n83\t- **Use const** — `const` constructor wherever possible\n84\t- **Trailing commas** — on every parameter list\n85\t\n86\t## Success Criteria\n87\t\n88\t- `lib/screens/weight_nutrition/weight_nutrition_screen.dart` exists with valid Dart\n89\t- Uses `Theme.of(context)` for all styling (colors, text, shapes)\n90\t- No hardcoded colors, text styles, or spacing values\n91\t- Route added to `app_router.dart`\n92\t- `dart analyze` passes"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8398349f-11ff-4ed6-8769-277ecd25967f","uuid":"be01fdfa-7b40-4a34-9cca-02df2d470f95","timestamp":"2026-05-19T00:17:52.729Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/minh/Documents/openplayboosks/examples/baby-app/.converge/journal/default/tasks/006-weight-nutrition-03-convert/attempts/wip/TASK.md","content":"# Task: 006-weight-nutrition-03-convert\n\n# Convert: Weight & Nutrition\n\nConvert the constrained HTML design to a pixel-perfect Flutter widget using the **stitch-flutter** skill.\n\n## Inputs\n- `.stitch/designs/weight-nutrition/design.html` — HTML design mockup (written in Flutter HTML Glossary vocabulary)\n- `.stitch/designs/weight-nutrition/SPEC.md` — Screen specification\n- `.stitch/system/DESIGN.md` — Design system specification\n\n## How It Works\n\nThe HTML mockup uses the **Flutter HTML Glossary** — a constrained vocabulary where every HTML class and `data-*` attribute maps 1:1 to a Flutter widget. This enables mechanical, pixel-perfect conversion.\n\n## Conversion Steps\n\n1. **Read HTML** — Parse `.stitch/designs/weight-nutrition/design.html` and extract:\n   - `:root` CSS tokens → update `lib/theme/app_theme.dart` if new tokens found\n   - `.scaffold` element tree → this is the conversion entry point\n   - `data-*` attributes → Flutter widget parameters\n   - `data-animate` attributes → `flutter_animate` chains\n   - `aria-*` attributes → `Semantics` widgets\n\n2. **Walk the DOM** — Process each glossary element top-down:\n   - `.scaffold` → `Scaffold()`\n   - `.app-bar` → `AppBar()`\n   - `.column` → `Column()`\n   - `.row` → `Row()`\n   - `.card` → `Card()`\n   - `.ink-well[data-route]` → `InkWell(onTap: () => context.push(route))`\n   - `.network-image` → `CachedNetworkImage()`\n   - `.icon[data-name]` → `Icon(Icons.{name})`\n   - Text classes (`.title-large`, `.body-medium`, etc.) → `Text(..., style: textTheme.X)`\n   - `data-color` → `colorScheme.X`\n   - `data-spacing` → `AppTheme.spaceX`\n   - `data-radius` → `AppTheme.radiusX`\n\n3. **Generate Dart** — Write `lib/screens/weight_nutrition/weight_nutrition_screen.dart`:\n   ```dart\n   import 'package:flutter/material.dart';\n   import 'package:cached_network_image/cached_network_image.dart';\n   import 'package:flutter_animate/flutter_animate.dart';\n   import 'package:folio/theme/app_theme.dart';\n\n   class WeightNutritionScreen extends StatelessWidget {\n     const WeightNutritionScreen({super.key});\n\n     @override\n     Widget build(BuildContext context) {\n       final theme = Theme.of(context);\n       final colorScheme = theme.colorScheme;\n       final textTheme = theme.textTheme;\n\n       return Scaffold(\n         // ... mechanically converted from glossary elements\n       );\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Update router** — Add route to `lib/router/app_router.dart`:\n   ```dart\n   GoRoute(\n     path: '/weight-nutrition',\n     builder: (context, state) => const WeightNutritionScreen(),\n   ),\n   ```\n\n5. **Verify** — Run `dart analyze lib/screens/weight_nutrition/weight_nutrition_screen.dart`\n\n## Reference Skills\n\n- Read **flutter-building-layouts** for constraint rules (constraints down, sizes up), avoiding unbounded constraints in flex boxes, and when to use `Expanded` vs `Flexible` vs `SizedBox`.\n- Read **flutter-animating-apps** for Hero transition setup, implicit vs explicit animations, and staggered animation patterns.\n\n## Quality Gates\n\n- **No hardcoded colors** — `Color(0xFF...)` and `Colors.blue` are banned; use `colorScheme.X`\n- **No hardcoded text styles** — `TextStyle(fontSize: 16)` is banned; use `textTheme.X`\n- **No hardcoded spacing** — `EdgeInsets.all(16)` is banned; use `AppTheme.spaceMd`\n- **No Container abuse** — prefer `SizedBox`, `Padding`, `DecoratedBox` when Container is overkill\n- **Use const** — `const` constructor wherever possible\n- **Trailing commas** — on every parameter list\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- `lib/screens/weight_nutrition/weight_nutrition_screen.dart` exists with valid Dart\n- Uses `Theme.of(context)` for all styling (colors, text, shapes)\n- No hardcoded colors, text styles, or spacing values\n- Route added to `app_router.dart`\n- `dart analyze` passes","numLines":92,"startLine":1,"totalLines":92}}}
