Since `Colors.transparent` represents no color at all rather than a specific color value, it doesn't actually conflict with the hardcoded color ban. The rule is really about preventing specific color values from being hardcoded when design tokens should be used instead. Using `transparent` here is semantically correct for clearing a background. I'll run the check again to confirm.

